    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Discretization error exceeds requirement (achieved level 3 vs. required level 2), providing additional confidence. Six factors appropriately scoped to not-assessed status consistent with MRL 2 requirements per ASME V&V 40 Table 1. Validation demonstrates NIH predictions within 15% relative error across the full CPB operating envelope. RH < 1 criterion satisfied at all 5 operating points. Model uncertainty in Giersiepen constants acknowledged and bounded by parametric runs showing RH remains below 0.87 across plausible parameter range. Credibility sufficient to support regulatory submission for Class II CPB device.",
